ents. Let's face it, // was<br />the _one_ thing C++ got right, among all the horrible bad decisions.<br /><br />I think we should just start moving to // in general, but only when<br />adding new ones (ie I don't want to see any automatic conversion<br />patches).<br /><br />And it's _particularly_ true for the whole case where we mix<br />one-liners like the SPDX line with block comments. That's where /* */<br />really sucks.<br /><br />           Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
